inage this monograph is dedicated to a dialogue between ethnographic findings and theoretical ideas,, and explores how we may rethink common conceptions of religious normativity.  afunded by University of Toronto Libraries  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian lifevCase studieszBrazil. 0aChristian lifevCase studieszGhana. 0aChristian lifevCase studieszKenya. 0aChristian lifevCase studieszSwitzerland. 0aChristian lifezBrazilvCase studies. 0aChristian lifezGhanavCase studies. 0aChristian lifezKenyavCase studies. 0aChristian lifezSwitzerlandvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aPentecostalism and Christian renewal movements.  aanthropology of religion.  acontemporary Christianity.  aconversion.  aeveryday religion.  alived religion.  areligious butinage.  areligious identity.  areligious mobility.1 aDroz, Yvan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRey, Jeanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut2 aUniversity of Toronto Librariesefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487541835zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487541835zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487541835/original  a978-3-11-073922-0 University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127221-4 ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-all